                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–1548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Krentz</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 16, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. Apropos of your 81 Nov 15,<note n="11" xml:id="d780fn11">Not printed.</note>
                    Dept has received unconfirmed reports indicating that Taipei is being thought of
                    as possible point to which remove ChiGovt or at any rate to which substantial
                    number of Govt personnel could repair. Have you seen any manifestations on spot
                    of preparations to these ends? Has Governor Wei<note n="12" xml:id="d780fn12"
                        >Wei Tao-ming.</note> given you any indication of his thinking or any
                    independent planning on his part if for example the Govt moves to Canton and is
                    subsequently <pb facs="0864" n="854" xml:id="pg_854"/> engulfed? Dept does not
                    intend that you should raise this matter with Governor Wei but merely seeks any
                    info you may have and would welcome any suggestions you may have to offer.<note
                        n="13" xml:id="d780fn13">The Consul General at Taipei replied in telegram
                        No. 83, November 18 3 p. m.: “No signs preparations any kind.”
                        (893.00/11–1848)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
